msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:11
msgid "Using ANARI with VTK"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:13
msgid ""
"ANARI can be enabled via the CMake variable "
"`VTK_MODULE_ENABLE_VTK_RenderingAnari=YES`. VTK requires an installation of "
"the ANARI-SDK library. The path to the ANARI-SDK installation directory has "
"to be given with the following CMake variable `anari_DIR=<path-to-anari-"
"install-directory>`. VTK requires a version of ANARI-SDK with a minimum "
"version of `v0.9.1`. The repository can be found on [GitHub](https://github."
"com/KhronosGroup/ANARI-SDK/tree/v0.14.1)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:15
msgid ""
"Specific build instructions for your chosen platform are provided in "
"[Building ANARI-SDK from Source](https://github.com/KhronosGroup/ANARI-SDK/"
"blob/v0.14.1/README.md#building-the-sdk-from-source)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:17
msgid ""
"ANARI's backend can be chosen at runtime by providing the following "
"environment variable: `ANARI_LIBRARY=<backend-name>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:19
msgid ""
"**Note**: If the library is not installed system-wide, the `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` "
"may also need to be specified with the path to the backend built library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:21
msgid ""
"The following sections show some backends that were tested in VTK with their "
"corresponding version and dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:25
msgid "ANARI-VisRTX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:27
msgid ""
"The required version for VisRTX is `v0.11.0` with ANARI `v0.14.1`. The "
"repository with the VisRTX sources can be found on [GitHub](https://github."
"com/NVIDIA/VisRTX/tree/v0.11.0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:29
msgid ""
"To run an application using ANARI-VisRTX the name of the anari library is "
"`ANARI_LIBRARY=visrtx`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:33
msgid "ANARI-OSPRay"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:35
msgid ""
"The OSPRay backend repository for ANARI can be found on [GitHub](https://"
"github.com/ospray/anari-ospray). It is highly recommanded to use the "
"internal superbuild for this repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:37
msgid ""
"With the changes applied in the superbuild CMake file, the build can be "
"achieved by calling the follwing lines:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../modules/vtk-modules/Rendering/ANARI/README.md:39
msgid ""
"To run an application using ANARI-OSPRay the name of the anari library is "
"`ANARI_LIBRARY=ospray`."
msgstr ""
